<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-467-311  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 467 311.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 1 1990 v7 n38 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Nakamichi rolls out 3 1/2-inch rewritable optical disk drive.andO;(Nakamichi Mass Optical Storage Technologies's RMD-5100-S)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Patch, Kimberly.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mass Optical Storage Technologies Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Mass Optical Storage Technologies RMD-5100-S (Optical disk drive)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMagneto-Optical Disk DrivesErasable Optical Memory.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Nakamichi rolls out 3-1/2-inch rewritable optical disk driveandM;CYPRESS, Calif -- Nakamichi's recently formed data storage subsidiary MassOptical Storage Technologies (Most) has announced what it claims is the first3-1/2-inch removable rewritable magneto-optical disk drive on the market.andM;The Most RMD-5100-S is the first in a series of small erasable opticaldrives, according to Most officials.andM;The disk drive holds 128MB of formatted data, and has an average access timeof 47 milliseconds (ms), an average seek time of 35ms, and a data transferrate of 512KB per second with 1.5MB per second bursts in asynchronous modeand 3MB bursts in synchronous mode, according to officials.andM;The RMD-5100-S drive has a fine voice coil in addition to the regular voicecoil, giving it a 9ms seek time when finding information near the track it isalready on, according to Most President Eric Swartz.andM;&quot;The drive actuator has two components to it: a large coil like a traditionaldrive and also a fine positioner that moves only the lens instead of thewhole assembly back and forth,&quot; Swartz said.andP;  &quot;It can go plus or minus 64tracks very quickly.&quot;andM;The drive is packaged in a 5-1/4-inch form factor, and will fit into ahalf-slot, 5-1/4-inch spot on a workstation or PC.andM;The RMD-5100-S drive will be available next month, priced at about $1,500.andO;Prices for the 3-1/2-inch optical disk cartridges are expected to be about$120 each, according to officials.andM;For additional information about the RMD-5100-S drive, Mass Optical StorageTechnologies Inc. can be contacted at 11205 Knott Ave., Suite B, Cypress, CA90630, (714) 898 9400.andO;</TEXT></DOC>